cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for analyzing word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves analyzing the embedding space, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of unsupervised learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also involves analyzing the semantic content of word embeddings, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of NLP applications, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the representation of rare senses in word embeddings, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
